cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

This paper deals with the task of retrieving patents with similar claims, which is a typical information retrieval problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also uses NLP methods to parse text, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions that it uses a qualitative analysis of the writing style of the claims, which could be related to cs.LG (Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with legal texts, which could be related to cs.CY (Cryptography and Security).
